Account Deletion Policy – DenTool:
At DenTool, we respect users' control over their personal data. This policy explains how users can request deletion of their account and associated data. 
1. How to Request Account Deletion 
Users may request deletion of their DenTool account through in the following method: 
Inside the Application 
Users can request account deletion by navigating to: 
Settings → Account → Delete Account 
2. Data That May Be Retained 
Certain information may be retained for a limited period if necessary for: 
• legal obligations  
• resolving disputes  
• preventing fraud or abuse  
This data will not be used for marketing purposes. 
4. Effect of Account Deletion 
Once the account is deleted: 
• the user will no longer be able to log in  
• order history may be removed  
• previously stored preferences will be deleted  
If the user wishes to use DenTool again, a new account must be created. 
